sentences.english: No e-mail newsletters clutter your mailbox.
sentences.chinese: 没有塞满您邮箱的电子邮件时事通讯。

sentences.english: The Apple support Web site filled up with messages from apoplectic customers.
sentences.chinese: Apple客服网站塞满了愤怒的用户投诉邮件。

sentences.english: Their computer's hard drive was crammed with snapshots of wild beasts-winged, clawed, and hoofed.
sentences.chinese: 连电脑硬盘里也塞满了野生禽兽的照片。

sentences.english: The bed is stuffed with cotton so it was very soft.
sentences.chinese: 这张床里塞满了棉花，因此很柔软。

sentences.english: When he gets home, Lori's at the table, mouth full of chips.
sentences.chinese: 当他回到家，劳瑞正坐在桌前，嘴里塞满了薯条。

sentences.english: She has come back with her backpack filled with interesting picture-books.
sentences.chinese: 她已经回来了，背包里塞满了有趣的图书。

sentences.english: Each time I went to see her, my grandma would fill my pockets with sweets .
sentences.chinese: 每次我去看奶奶，她总是在我的衣兜塞满糖果。

sentences.english: The road was chock a - block with varieties of vehicles again today.
sentences.chinese: 马路上今天又塞满各种车辆了。

sentences.english: I tried to say something，but my mouth was full of cotton wool.
sentences.chinese: 我想说句话，但我嘴里塞满了药棉。

sentences.english: Their classroom is chocked up with desks and chairs.
sentences.chinese: 他们的教室里塞满了书桌和椅子。

sentences.english: An almond tart, stuffed with the sweet, ripe fruit.
sentences.chinese: 杏仁挞，里头塞满了熟透的甜蜜水果。

sentences.english: The parking lot was jammed with cars.
His pockets were lumped with various articles.
sentences.chinese: 他的口袋里塞满了各种小东西。

sentences.english: Finally we preserve the skin, fill up the animal with stuffing and sew it up.
sentences.chinese: 最后我们保存皮肤，用填料塞满它的肚子和缝好肚子。

sentences.english: The city's museums are filled with mouldy old collections.
sentences.chinese: 市内博物馆中塞满老旧乏味的收藏品。

sentences.english: The bonded warehouse is filled with many kinds of licensed goods.
sentences.chinese: 这个海关保税仓库里塞满了各种保税货物。
